50|$|A beanpot is a deep, <b>wide-bellied,</b> short-necked vessel used to cook bean-based dishes. Beanpots are {{typically}} made of ceramic, though pots made of other materials, like cast iron, {{can also be}} found. The relatively narrow mouth of the beanpot minimizes evaporation and heat loss, while the deep, wide, thick-walled body of the pot facilitates long, slow cooking times.|$|E

